ou a slight indication of who you&#8217;re calling or texting, but wouldn&#8217;t it be nice if all your iPhone contacts had photos to go with them? Here&#8217;s how to manually add a picture to a contact.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253370/how-to-manually-add-a-photo-to-a-contact-on-an-iphone-or-ipad/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/AaZgMnTzpCg\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462371840,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253370'),(18,2,'How to Find Out If Your Device Is Running 32-Bit or 64-Bit Android','http://www.howtogeek.com/253461/how-to-find-out-if-your-device-is-running-32-bit-or-64-bit-android/','Cameron Summerson','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/62a52831d9717054299dab6fe596180f/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/IMG_8352-650x300.jpg\" /></p><p>There comes a time in every Android user’s life when an important question has to be answered: is my device running a 32- or 64-bit operating system? It can be a rough, troubling time if you’re not sure how to answer that question. But we’re here for you, and we’ll help walk you through what to do should such a scenario arise. Just breathe, it’s going to be fine.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253461/how-to-find-out-if-your-device-is-running-32-bit-or-64-bit-android/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/Gm4q3TMBNC8\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462375380,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253461'),(19,2,'How to Organize Your Email with Smart Mailboxes in Apple Mail','http://www.howtogeek.com/252635/how-to-organize-your-email-with-smart-mailboxes-in-apple-mail/','Matt Klein','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/b52dee16e7072fa0b9080755ea5f136f/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/img_5723f9223c1c7.png\" /></p><p>One of the more intriguing features of Apple Mail is smart mailboxes, which collate your mail according to a predetermined set of rules. You mail doesn&#8217;t actually get moved to these smart mailboxes, it just appears as though it is.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/252635/how-to-organize-your-email-with-smart-mailboxes-in-apple-mail/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/yC2vHjK_NFI\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462379640,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=252635'),(20,2,'Geek Trivia: For Decades, European Countries Kept Rabid Fox Populations In Check With?','http://www.howtogeek.com/trivia/for-decades-european-countries-kept-rabid-fox-populations-in-check-with/','Jason Fitzpatrick','<p><img src=\"http://cdn8.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/gg/up/sshot542ef4d2a58a8.png\" /></p><table width=\"650px\" border=\"0\"><tr><td><h3><a href=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/trivia/for-decades-european-countries-kept-rabid-fox-populations-in-check-with/\">For Decades, European Countries Kept Rabid Fox Populations In Check With?</a></h3></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"><ol><li> Snipers</li><li> Chicken Heads</li><li> Vaccine Traps</li><li> Mass Sterilization</li></ol><p>Think you know the answer?</p></td></tr></table><em><p><a href=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/trivia/for-decades-european-countries-kept-rabid-fox-populations-in-check-with/\"><img src=\"http://cdn8.howtogeek.com/geekers/up/readmore-button.png\" border=\"0\" /></a></p></em><p></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/AQ1KysnhEwM\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462383422,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?post_type=trivia&p=253289'),(21,2,'How to Send Your Amazon Echo Shopping List to Your Email','http://www.howtogeek.com/251967/how-to-send-your-amazon-echo-shopping-list-to-your-email/','Craig Lloyd','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/4b9d651787e8b46c391ed18f39ad2334/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/IMG_2351_stomped-650x301.jpg\" /></p><p>If you&#8217;ve been using the Amazon Echo to add things to your grocery list, here&#8217;s how to send that list to your email when you&#8217;re finally ready to go shopping.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/251967/how-to-send-your-amazon-echo-shopping-list-to-your-email/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/I7WO4wVTsTE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462388400,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=251967'),(22,2,'What to Do If You Can’t Receive Text Messages From iPhone Users','http://www.howtogeek.com/252100/what-to-do-if-you-cant-receive-text-messages-from-iphone-users/','Chris Hoffman','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/90ef29fdb71f178e0bf0fa5b586a5214/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/img_571d763672bc4.jpg\" /></p><p>If you&#8217;ve been having trouble receiving text messages from iPhone users, Apple&#8217;s iMessage is probably at fault&#8211;especially if you recently switched from iPhone to Android, or something else.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/252100/what-to-do-if-you-cant-receive-text-messages-from-iphone-users/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/3VEzGHoVvwE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462392240,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=252100'),(23,2,'How to See If Your VPN Is Leaking Your Personal Information','http://www.howtogeek.com/253475/how-to-see-if-your-vpn-is-leaking-your-personal-information/','Jason Fitzpatrick','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/cf7de49adb0e052ca27f8f71dafa13df/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/img_5729384d3f226.jpg\" /></p><p>Many people use Virtual Private Networks (VPNs) to mask their identity, encrypt their communications, or browse the web from a different location. All those goals can fall apart if your real information is leaking through a security hole, which is more common than you&#8217;d think. Let&#8217;s look at how to identify and patch those leaks.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253475/how-to-see-if-your-vpn-is-leaking-your-personal-information/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/Dfb6fGmB4eQ\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462444840,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253475'),(24,2,'How to Allow a Standard Windows 10 User to Change the Time and Date','http://www.howtogeek.com/253745/how-to-allow-a-standard-windows-10-user-to-change-the-time-and-date/','Walter Glenn','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/125361e7dc0a641b435d670da73f2713/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/wdt_top-650x300.png\" /></p><p>By default, only users with administrator rights in Windows 10 can change time and date settings. If you&#8217;re using Windows 10 Professional or Enterprise edition, however, you can use Group Policy to allow standard users to change the time and date. Here&#8217;s how to do it.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253745/how-to-allow-a-standard-windows-10-user-to-change-the-time-and-date/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/oTurWDcm9gA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462449600,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253745'),(25,2,'How to Enable One-Handed Mode in Android’s Google Keyboard','http://www.howtogeek.com/253432/how-to-enable-one-handed-mode-in-androids-google-keyboard/','Cameron Summerson','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/f672251a8a3338dfe60816a875e1b15e/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/IMG_8348-1-650x300.jpg\" /></p><p>We’ve all been in a situation where one hand or the other simply isn’t available for responding to a text message, and with the ever-increasing size of Android phones, that’s starting to become more of an issue. The good news is that Google Keyboard now has a much-needed feature: One-Handed Mode.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253432/how-to-enable-one-handed-mode-in-androids-google-keyboard/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/yvpe0vk7gDw\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462453200,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253432'),(26,2,'How to Add a Calculator to Microsoft Word','http://www.howtogeek.com/253333/how-to-add-a-calculator-to-microsoft-word/','Lori Kaufman','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/7e9174d067c1c5199296035abdb96a9e/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/00_lead_image_calculator_in_word-1.png\" /></p><p>To do basic arithmetic in Word, you normally have to open the Windows calculator to get your answers, then manually insert them into Word. However, there is a third-party add-in for Word that provides a popup calculator that will calculate numbers in your document, and automatically insert the answer.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253333/how-to-add-a-calculator-to-microsoft-word/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/5pB3ueKDoqs\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462458240,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253333'),(27,2,'How to Rename Files from the Save Dialog in OS X','http://www.howtogeek.com/253236/how-to-rename-files-from-the-save-dialog-in-os-x/','Matt Klein','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/0cf5716dae22e0c22ad37a76477bc53a/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/img_5728bdf7bbbd5.png\" /></p><p>OS X is a great, finely polished operating system, but it&#8217;s not without its flaws. For years, there has been no way to rename files from the Save dialog&#8211;until now.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253236/how-to-rename-files-from-the-save-dialog-in-os-x/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/p6_mu2hBd2c\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462466040,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253236'),(28,2,'Geek Trivia: The Only Natural Lake In The World That Drains Into Two Oceans Is?','http://www.howtogeek.com/trivia/the-only-natural-lake-in-the-world-that-drains-into-two-oceans-is/','Jason Fitzpatrick','<p><img src=\"http://cdn8.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/gg/up/sshot542ef4d2a58a8.png\" /></p><table width=\"650px\" border=\"0\"><tr><td><h3><a href=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/trivia/the-only-natural-lake-in-the-world-that-drains-into-two-oceans-is/\">The Only Natural Lake In The World That Drains Into Two Oceans Is?</a></h3></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"><ol><li> Lake Victoria</li><li> Gatun Lake</li><li> Isa Lake</li><li> Lake Superior</li></ol><p>Think you know the answer?</p></td></tr></table><em><p><a href=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/trivia/the-only-natural-lake-in-the-world-that-drains-into-two-oceans-is/\"><img src=\"http://cdn8.howtogeek.com/geekers/up/readmore-button.png\" border=\"0\" /></a></p></em><p></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/p2GtJw1WDrQ\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462469838,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?post_type=trivia&p=253711'),(29,2,'How to View Your Nest Thermostat’s Usage History','http://www.howtogeek.com/251340/how-to-view-your-nest-thermostat%e2%80%99s-usage-history/','Craig Lloyd','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/b504b61853a1861fedc15c7084651eb1/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/IMG_2848-copy-650x300.jpg\" /></p><p>If you&#8217;re curious about how often your heat or air conditioning is on throughout the day, you can actually look at your Nest&#8217;s usage history to see when things were running, as well as see what the temperature was set it at a particular time during the day.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/251340/how-to-view-your-nest-thermostat%e2%80%99s-usage-history/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/UPwmKA2p1IY\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462474800,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=251340'),(30,2,'How Smart or Efficient Could a Workplace Office Network Be?','http://www.howtogeek.com/253199/how-smart-or-efficient-could-a-workplace-office-network-be/','Akemi Iwaya','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/689443dc7e3226dfbf02fab7ca92050b/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/how-smart-or-efficient-could-a-workplace-office-network-be-00.jpg\" /></p><p>When you set up a network in your office, and depending on the equipment and setup used, just how smart and/or efficient could that network actually be? Today&#8217;s SuperUser Q&amp;A post has the answer to a curious reader&#8217;s question.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253199/how-smart-or-efficient-could-a-workplace-office-network-be/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/Mf0t9AIqS-I\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462478675,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253199'),(31,2,'How to Create Custom Ringtones for Your Android Phone','http://www.howtogeek.com/252565/how-to-create-custom-ringtones-for-your-android-phone/','Cameron Summerson','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/eef9c35c6784420c1d16e69c833544a8/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/IMG_8305-650x300.jpg\" /></p><p>So you got a shiny new Android phone. You changed the wallpaper, bought a case that you like, arranged your home screens…you know, made it yours. Then someone calls. Why on earth are you still using a stock ringtone? Get that out of here—it’s time to not only make it look like yours, but sound like it too.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/252565/how-to-create-custom-ringtones-for-your-android-phone/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/DcyUfGPFyFo\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462531200,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=252565'),(32,2,'How to Create an iOS Configuration Profile and Alter Hidden Settings','http://www.howtogeek.com/253325/how-to-create-an-ios-configuration-profile-and-alter-hidden-settings/','Chris Hoffman','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/5db9461a87f7965e5cbb2cdff8575c84/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/img_5728109b09ec1.png\" /></p><p>Configuration profiles on an iPhone or iPad are sort of like Group Policy or the registry editor on Windows. They allow you to quickly distribute groups of settings and access powerful management features that aren&#8217;t normally available. Configuration profiles are really designed for organizations, but can be used by anyone.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253325/how-to-create-an-ios-configuration-profile-and-alter-hidden-settings/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/J9D6kdhcgDE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462536000,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253325'),(33,2,'How to Keep Netflix from Using All Your Phone’s Data','http://www.howtogeek.com/253844/how-to-keep-netflix-from-using-all-your-phones-data/','Matt Klein','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/525862d8867765d88a99787624213488/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/img_572b9a1a4ae70.png\" /></p><p>Netflix recently updated its mobile app with a long-awaited feature: now, you can specify how much data (approximately) it uses, so you don&#8217;t go over your cellular data cap.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253844/how-to-keep-netflix-from-using-all-your-phones-data/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/x-9sUszTI7o\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462539600,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253844'),(34,2,'How to Customize the Title Bar Theme in Microsoft Office 2016','http://www.howtogeek.com/253565/how-to-customize-the-title-bar-theme-in-microsoft-office-2016/','Lori Kaufman','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/c53696f3fe8ec18f858f8c97d31a1eaf/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/00_lead_image_customizing_title_bar.png\" /></p><p>Among the new features in Microsoft Office 2016 are some improvements to the user interface. For example, they added a background image to the title bar in each Office program, and an improved dark theme. Customizing the background and theme is easy, and we’ll show you how to do it.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/253565/how-to-customize-the-title-bar-theme-in-microsoft-office-2016/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/-dN8n0dmo-Y\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462544640,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=253565'),(35,2,'How to Adjust Overscan on the SHIELD Android TV','http://www.howtogeek.com/251934/how-to-adjust-overscan-on-the-shield-android-tv/','Cameron Summerson','<p><img src=\"http://www.howtogeek.com/thumbcache/580/230/897776ba7deb75055005b7cde9ed4ff0/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Settings_20160422_101552-1-650x300.png\" /></p><p>If you have an older TV and an NVIDIA SHIELD Android TV, you may notice that some content gets cut off around the edges. This is called overscan, and it can be incredibly annoying in a number of situations, not excluding one of SHIELD’s primary features: gaming. Fortunately, it’s an easy fix.</p><p><h3><a href=\'http://www.howtogeek.com/251934/how-to-adjust-overscan-on-the-shield-android-tv/\'>Click Here to Continue Reading</a></h3></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowToGeek/~4/_4lLp1WeilE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>',1462548180,'http://www.howtogeek.com/?p=251934');
